The paper deals with context-free grammars and their normal forms, which are topics closely related to formal languages (cs.FL) and automata theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Chomsky-Schutzenberger theorem, which is a result in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses graphical approaches to refine a regular language, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or machine learning (cs.LG).
